{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"immoveable-tanned-snail","description":"## Why\n\nThe code-review `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar (`code_review_result_v1`) persists only the SURFACED findings\nâ€” the `blocking`, `advisory`, and `coaching` buckets â€” and omits the dropped / indeterminate /\noverflow findings that pass-3 produced. It also does not persist the numeric\n`block_threshold`/`blocking_enabled` each finding was judged against. So \"the complete pass-1 finding\nlist\" is not recoverable for a code review, unlike plan review.\n\n## What\n\nExtend the code-review sidecar to `code_review_result_v2`, pooling ALL buckets (surfaced + dropped +\nindeterminate + overflow) with each finding's full pass-2 verification and pass-3 determination, plus\nthe resolved threshold/blocking_enabled â€” matching the plan-review sidecar's fidelity.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py` â€” bump `SCHEMA` to `code_review_result_v2`; in\n  `build_payload`, pool every bucket the verdict carries (not just blocking/advisory/coaching), each\n  finding with its verification + pass-3 fields + evidence/scenarios + resolved threshold; keep the\n  existing change metadata (`change_id`/`revision`/`change_fingerprint`) and `deps`;\n  `latest_code_review_result` accepts both `code_review_result_v1` and `_v2`.\n\n## Approach rationale\n\nMirror story A's plan-review enrichment on the code-review sidecar so both share one fidelity\nstandard and one reader shape, rather than inventing a code-specific record â€” the code-review gate\nalready runs the identical four-pass kernel, so its findings already carry the pass-2/pass-3 fields;\nthey are simply not all being written.\n\n## Compatibility & rollback\n\n`v1` code-review sidecars remain readable (new fields/buckets absent). The novelty-floor reader that\nconsumes surfaced findings keeps returning the surfaced union, so region-gating is unaffected. No\nbackfill; reverting restores the `v1` payload.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A code review that produces dropped/indeterminate findings emits a `code_review_result_v2`\n      event whose payload includes those buckets, each finding with its verification, pass-3\n      determination, and resolved threshold. Oracle: an integration test driving the sidecar `emit`\n      with a verdict containing all buckets and asserting on the emitted event JSON.\n- [ ] `latest_code_review_result` reads both a `v1` and a `v2` code-review sidecar. Oracle: a unit\n      test with one hand-written record of each schema.\n- [ ] The novelty-floor surfaced-findings reader returns exactly the blocking+advisory union from a\n      `v2` payload, unchanged vs an equivalent `v1` payload. Oracle: a unit test comparing the two.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.","id":"7c84-40dc-c112-410c","parent_id":"ba33-2310-f6c6-4bd6","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"code-review sidecar -> lossless v2 (all buckets + thresholds)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784067234905044001,"uuid":"e7b12717-ffa5-414d-9c6c-45269a1d2c84"}